   <abstract>The recto depicts Joe Clark in his older years, playing a banjo, sitting in a chair, outside and leaning against a log-cabin. Recto is signed as follows: Always, Old Joe Clark (?). Verso reads: A Living Legend Old Joe Clark, star of film an T.V., Carnegie Hall concert artist and ece of the naturally famous Renfro Valley Barn Dance each Saturday night, is shown in the old log-cabin setting of Renfro Valley, the Saturday night Bar Dance is broadcast throughout America. Renfro Valley is located on U. S. 25 between Berea and Mt. Vernon (just of I 75) and only an hour's drive south of Lexington, Ky.</abstract>
